Let us denote by $\Lambda_{\lambda}$ the set of points whose orbits are bounded under $T_{s}$. 
The following theorem was first proven 
in \cite{S87} for the Fibonacci Hamiltonian. 

\begin{thm}[Theorem 4.1 of \cite{M}]
The set $\Lambda_{\lambda}$ 
 is a compact locally maximal $T_{s}$-invariant transitive hyperbolic subset of $S_{\lambda}$, and 
 the periodic points of $T_{s}$ form a dense subset of $\Lambda_{\lambda}$.
 \end{thm}

We also have the following: 

\begin{thm}[Corollary 2.5 of \cite{DPW}]\label{thm2.3}
The forward semi-orbit of a point $p \in S_{\lambda}$ is bounded if and only if $p$ 
lies on the stable lamination of $\Lambda_{\lambda}$.
\end{thm}

